<H1>Images</H1>

<P>The <I>Image</I> menu provides access to all image-specific
functions in <I><B>flPhoto</B></I>:

<UL>

	<LI><A HREF="#open">Open</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#edit">Edit</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#save">Save</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#saveas">Save As...</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="print.html">Print...</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#selectall">Select All</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#selectnone">Select None</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#remove">Remove</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#revert">Revert</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#touchup">Touch-Up</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#transform">Transform</A></LI>

</UL>

<H2><A NAME="open">Open</A></H2>

<P>Choose <I>Open</I> to open the currently selected image in
the display area. If multiple images have been selected in the
album, then the last image that was selected will be opened.

<P>Images may also be opened by double-clicking on them in the
album.

<H2><A NAME="edit">Edit</A></H2>

<P>Choose <I>Edit</I> to edit the currently selected image with
the image editor of your choice; the default editor is "gimp".
If multiple images have been selected in the album, then the
last image that was selected will be edited.

<H2><A NAME="save">Save</A></H2>

<P>Choose <I>Save</I> to save the current image in the same
format. Currently <I><B>flPhoto</B></I> supports saving images
in the JPEG and PNG formats.

<P>If you rotate a JPEG image, <I><B>flPhoto</B></I> can save
the image without re-compressing it, so you won't lose quality.
If you perform other transformations or touch-up operations,
then the image will be re-compressed.

<P>When saving JPEG files, the JPEG parameter dialog will be
shown before the file is saved.

<CENTER><IMG SRC="jpeg.jpg" WIDTH="346" HEIGHT="323" ALT="The
JPEG Parameter Dialog"></CENTER>

<H2><A NAME="saveas">Save As...</A></H2>

<P>Choose <I>Save As...</I> to save the current image to a new
file.

<H2><A NAME="selectall">Select All</A></H2>

<P>Choose <I>Select All</I> to select all images in the album.

<H2><A NAME="selectnone">Select None</A></H2>

<P>Choose <I>Select None</I> to unselect all images in the album.

<H2><A NAME="remove">Remove</A></H2>

<P>Choose <I>Remove</I> to remove all selected images from the
album. Images are only removed from the album - the files
themselves remain on disk.

<H2><A NAME="revert">Revert</A></H2>

<P>Choose <I>Revert</I> to return the current image to its
original appearance.

<H2><A NAME="touchup">Touch-Up</A></H2>

<P>The <I>Touch-Up</I> menu provides several basic image
enhancement functions:

<UL>

	<LI><A HREF="#autoadjust">Auto Adjust</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#levels">Brightness + Contrast</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#redeye">Remove Red-Eye</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#sharpen">Sharpen</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#blur">Blur</A></LI>

</UL>

<H3><A NAME="autoadjust">Auto Adjust</A></H3>

<P>Choose <I>Auto Adjust</I> to sharpen the image and adjust the
brightness and contrast.

<H3><A NAME="levels">Brightness + Contrast</A></H3>

<P>Choose <I>Brightness + Contrast</I> to automatically adjust
the brightness and contrast of the image.

<H3><A NAME="redeye">Remove Red-Eye</A></H3>

<P>Choose <I>Remove Red-Eye</I> to automatically remove bright red
spots in the image.

<P>The current algorithm converts the spots to grayscale and
darkens them somewhat. The spot size is not limited, so a bright
red shirt or other object in an image will also get converted.
Pointers to better algorithms and/or code to improve the
algorithm are welcome!

<H3><A NAME="sharpen">Sharpen</A></H3>

<P>Choose <I>Sharpen</I> to sharpen the image using the
so-called "unsharp mask" operation which first creates a blurred
version of the image and then sharpens the image based on the
difference.

<H3><A NAME="blur">Blur</A></H3>

<P>Choose <I>Blur</I> to blur the image.

<H2><A NAME="transform">Transform</A></H2>

<P>The <I>Transform</I> menu provides several basic image
transformation functions:

<UL>

	<LI><A HREF="#crop">Crop...</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#rotate">Rotate Counter-Clockwise</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#rotate">Rotate Clockwise</A></LI>

	<LI><A HREF="#scale">Scale...</A></LI>

</UL>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="crop.jpg" WIDTH="371" HEIGHT="494" ALT="The
Image Crop Dialog"></CENTER>

<H3><A NAME="crop">Crop...</A></H3>

<P>Choose <I>Crop...</I> to display the image crop dialog. From
there you can enter <I>Left</I>, <I>Right</I>, <I>Top</I>, and
<I>Bottom</I> pixel margins or draw a rectangular area in the
preview box and then click <I>OK</I> to crop the current image
to the specified area. <I>All numbers are pixels.</I>

<H3><A NAME="rotate">Rotate (Counter-)Clockwise</A></H3>

<P>Choose <I>Rotate Counter-Clockwise</I> or <I>Rotate
Clockwise</I> to rotate the current image 90 degrees in the
specified direction.

<CENTER><IMG SRC="scale.jpg" WIDTH="341" HEIGHT="218" ALT="The
Image Scale Dialog"></CENTER>

<H3><A NAME="scale">Scale...</A></H3>

<P>Choose <I>Scale...</I> to diplay the image scale dialog. From
there you can enter new <I>Width</I>, <I>Height</I>, and
<I>Scale</I> values to control the size of the image. Click
<I>OK</I> to resize the image.

